    "description": "A systematic mesh convergence study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Element size was refined from 2.0 mm to 0.25 mm across five refinement levels. The Richardson extrapolation method was applied to quantify the grid convergence index (GCI) for construct stiffness and yield force predictions. Results demonstrated GCI values below 1.5% at the selected production mesh density (0.5 mm), confirming that discretization error is well controlled. This activity was performed prior to validation comparison runs and is referenced in the discretization error credibility factor assessment.",
